When I am inside an issue record, or when I look at a list of issues, whether in a filter or a dashboard, I often want to create a new issue that relates to an issue I am looking at.  It is often not a subtask, but a related issue - maybe a child, maybe an issue that is blocked by an issue I am looking at, or maybe simply a related issue.  It would make my workflow much smoother if I could create a linked issue in the same way I can create a subtask or assign a label - by click on the "More" button from within an existing issue, or clicking on the "Actions" down-arrow next to an issue when it appears in a list, rather than clicking on create issue, and linking to the existing issue from within the new issue.

Thanks,

Daniel.

